Crednen'a protophylloides Knowlton (Plate 8) Credneria protophyzzoides Knowlton, U. S. Geol. Surv. Prof. Paper 101, 267, pl. 46, 1917.

There is a single specimen and its counterpart and many incomplete specimens from Locality P. 375 which are similar in size and essential details to the type and figured specimens of this species from the Vermejo formation. The Medicine Bow specimen is somewhat larger than the figured Vermejo specimen, but is identical with the large, unfigured specimen described by Knowl- ton from the same formation.

There is nothing to be added at the present time to the accurate description and discussion of this species by Knowlton. He has already adequately pointed out the superficial resemblance of this species to several American species of Protophyllum, and its greater similarity to 3 number of European members of this genus. Comparable types appear to be rare in the late Cretaceous and early Tertiary of the Rocky Mountains.
